<sec>
<st>
Decline and death</st>
<p>

Mark Arnold-Forster suffered from persistent ill health in his fifties, in particular a series of minor strokes. In 1979, he developed cancer of the upper <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../350/59350.xml">
colon</link> and died at his home, 50 Clarendon Road, Notting Hill, London, on <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../237/6237.xml">
Christmas Day</link>, 1981. He was cremated at West London crematorium on <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../054/19279054.xml">
5 January</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../756/34756.xml">
1982</link>.</p>

